<HEADLINE>
FT  30 SEP 93 / London Stock Exchange: MGN stock placed
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOEL KIBAZO, CHRISTOPHER PRICE and SAQIB QURESHI
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The placing of the 54.8 per cent holding in Mirror Group Newspapers
belonging to the late Mr Robert Maxwell's private companies finally went
ahead yesterday, after a week of intensive pre-placing by brokers for the
companies' administrators. More than 219m shares were placed with a variety
of institutions, although the strike price of 170p was a little below that
which had been expected. The sale raised Pounds 373m.
One dealer involved in the placing reported that there was virtually no
stock coming back into the market from the offer and that this had been a
main plank in the share price's support yesterday. The stock closed at the
170p strike price, down 7. Media analysts said the stock was unlikely to go
very far in the short term as the whole sector fretted over the threat of
VAT on newspapers in the November budget, and the impact of the recent price
war among the press.
</TEXT>
