<HEADLINE>
FT  30 SEP 93 / International Company News: French exchange body fines Conso
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALICE RAWSTHORN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
THE French stock market authorities yesterday issued a harsh indictment of
Mr Pierre Conso, the prominent businessman who last year resigned as
chairman of the Ciments Francais cement group, after a scandal over the
discovery of FFr2bn (Dollars 354m) of off-balance sheet dealings, writes
Alice Rawsthorn.
He was also fined FFr400,000 for his part in the affair, which led to heavy
losses at the group.
