<HEADLINE>
FT  30 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Non-recurring costs put Starmin loss at
Pounds 1.24m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CATHERINE MILTON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
STARMIN, the quarry products company chaired by Lord Parkinson, the former
Conservative cabinet minister, announced interim pre-tax losses deepening
from Pounds 479,000 to Pounds 1.24m in the six months to June 30.
Mr Owen Rout, the acting chief executive, said the company had not so far
received notification of legal action by either Mr Raschid Abdullah, a
non-executive director who speaks for about 30 per cent of Starmin's equity,
or his brother Osman.
Mr Osman Abdullah said he had not reached a decision. His brother was not
available for comment.
Turnover fell to Pounds 8.59m (Pounds 10.8m) as the company continued its
programme of disposals of non-core businesses to bring down debt.
This is the first set of results since a review of accounting policies
prompted the company to restate 1992 pre-tax losses from Pounds 8.06m to
Pounds 11.9m in 1992. The restatement was prompted by a review of accounting
policies focused on asset swaps paid for with shares in a privately held
company.
On acquisitions, Mr Rout said: 'A number of talks are going on. Any option
we would look at. But we must be satisfied any deal is in the best interests
of shareholders.'
He said he would continue as acting chief executive for the time being:
'There is no point going out and looking for a new chief executive if we
then conclude a deal which makes his appointment unnecessary.'
Operating losses were Pounds 507,000 (Pounds 325,000), which disguised a
Pounds 10,000 (Pounds 1.16m) operating profit on continuing operations,
before exceptional costs, the company said. There were exceptional costs of
Pounds 388,000 (Pounds 1.57m), of which Pounds 250,000 covered the
reorganisation and board review while Pounds 138,000 covered abortive
acquisition costs.
Interest charges rose to Pounds 352,000 (Pounds 267,000) and net debt at the
half year end was Pounds 8.12m for gearing of 44.6 per cent.
Losses per share were 0.4p (0.3p) and the board did not declare a dividend.
It paid 0.1p last time.
</TEXT>
