<HEADLINE>
FT  30 SEP 93 / International Company News: Dollars 640m US placement for
Smurfit
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TIM COONE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   DUBLIN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
JEFFERSON Smurfit Group, the Dublin-based paper and packaging company, has
announced a private placement of Dollars 640m (Pounds 416m) in senior loan
notes with US investors, to refinance existing debt.
In what is thought to be one of the largest placements in this sector of the
US corporate securities market by a non-US group, 28 US institutions
participated in the issue, led by the Prudential Insurance Company of
America and the Annuity Association of America, which subscribed Dollars
104m each for the loan notes.
The notes have been issued in four tranches of 7,10,12 and 15 years, with an
average life of 10.1 years.
The issue has been split between the group's main international holding
company and its US arm.
</TEXT>
