<HEADLINE>
FT  30 SEP 93 / UK Company News: Fleming Far Eastern
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Fleming Far Eastern, the investment trust, has negotiated a loan of Dollars
90m (Pounds 58m) from a syndicate of banks.
It was arranged by Robert Fleming.
The loan, which will replace an existing Dollars 53m loan repayable on
September 30, is at a fixed interest rate of 5.69 per cent a year and is
repayable on September 30 1998.
