<HEADLINE>
FT  30 SEP 93 / Observer: Worthy suggestion
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Accountancy firm Touche Ross reckons that football clubs are underestimating
their assets by failing to disclose the value of players on their balance
sheets. The remedy, surprise, surprise, is to employ a professional valuer
to estimate players' worth and publish the figure in the accounts - someone
like, say, Touche Ross.
But when it comes to disclosing the fees Touche Ross charged Manchester
United for just such a service last year, the firm is rather less keen on
disclosure. 'It was done professionally, for a modest fee,' comes the
response.
