<HEADLINE>
FT  30 SEP 93 / People: Adding up for BT
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
British Telecommunications has played safe in its choice of a new finance
director, plumping for an accountant from inside the company.
Robert Brace, 43, moves to the top finance spot, with a seat on the BT
board, from the post of group controller - roughly equivalent to chief
accountant.
Brace joined BT four years ago as finance director of its UK division. He
was recruited from Black &amp; Decker, where he was vice president, business and
finance. Before that, he was Unipart's finance director, having moved into
industry from the then accountancy firm Peat Marwick Mitchell.
Brace's appointment follows the surprise departure of Barry Romeril, who
this summer moved to the US to become finance director of Xerox Corporation.
