FT  30 SEP 93 / Devonshire Names to sue over Pounds 154m loss
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ANDREW JACK
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MEMBERS of the loss-making Devonshire underwriting syndicates at the Lloyd's
of London insurance market voted yesterday to sue their members' and
managing agents for compensation. Losses to date on five syndicates are
Pounds 154m, Andrew Jack writes.
About 1,500 Names - individuals whose assets underwrite the market - on the
Devonshire Names Action Group supported calls for litigation for negligence
against their advisers for the 1989 and 1990 underwriting years. The Names
have still to decide whether to sue their brokers and auditors.
The group said the move was a precaution in case a Lloyd's attempt to settle
disputes with loss-making Names out of court was not satisfactory.
