<HEADLINE>
FT  29 SEP 93 / French government considers publicy owned company requests
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The French government is considering requests from publicly owned companies
for more than FFr20bn (Dollars 3.5bn) in new capital. In general it has
resisted large injections of capital in an attempt to limit the budget
deficit, targeted at FFr317bn this year.
According to the Ministry of Transport, Air France, the loss-making airline,
has requested about FFr5bn in recapitalisation, while Compagnie Generale de
Maritime wants FFr500m. Aerospatiale, the aerospace group, said yesterday
that it sought about FFr3bn to finance new programmes. Bull, the loss-making
computer manufacturer which is drawing up a restructuring plan, would not
confirm it wanted FFr9bn.
</TEXT>
